fileChanges.details:
Add rules that override --gradient-left, --gradient-right, and --accent-color on the .dynamic-content-carousel wrapper element, so that regardless of the page's accent color class, this block always uses neon-green gradient values. Specifically add:

.dynamic-content-carousel {
  --gradient-left: var(--color-neon-green);
  --gradient-right: var(--color-blue);
}

This leverages CSS specificity: the block-scoped custom properties will override the page-level accent color variants set by .blue, .yellow, .orange, .purple, .green classes in colors.css. The existing shared styles in swiper.css continue to reference --gradient-left and --gradient-right, but within .dynamic-content-carousel those will always resolve to neon-green/blue.
